
Overview of noun holler

The noun holler has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) bellow, bellowing, holla, holler, hollering, hollo, holloa, roar, roaring, yowl -- (a very loud utterance (like the sound of an animal); "his bellow filled the hallway")
2. hollow, holler -- (a small valley between mountains; "he built himself a cabin in a hollow high up in the Appalachians")

Overview of verb holler

The verb holler has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) holler, holler out -- (shout out; "He hollered out to surrender our weapons")
2. (2) shout, shout out, cry, call, yell, scream, holler, hollo, squall -- (utter a sudden loud cry; "she cried with pain when the doctor inserted the needle"; "I yelled to her from the window but she couldn't hear me")
3. (1) gripe, bitch, grouse, crab, beef, squawk, bellyache, holler -- (complain; "What was he hollering about?")
